    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " tgkill ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "sends the signal"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".I",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " sig"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "to the thread with the thread ID"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".I",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " tid"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "in the thread group"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".IR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " tgid ."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "(By contrast,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " kill (2)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "can be used to send a signal only to a process (i.e., thread group)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "as a whole, and the signal will be delivered to an arbitrary"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "thread within that process.)"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " tkill ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "is an obsolete predecessor to"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " tgkill ()."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "It allows only the target thread ID to be specified,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "which may result in the wrong thread being signaled if a thread"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "terminates and its thread ID is recycled."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Avoid using this system call."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "comment",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" FIXME Maybe say something about the following:"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" http://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=12889"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" Quoting Rich Felker <bugdal@aerifal.cx>:"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" There is a race condition in pthread_kill: it is possible that,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" between the time pthread_kill reads the pid/tid from the target"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" thread descriptor and the time it makes the tgkill syscall,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" the target thread terminates and the same tid gets assigned"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" to a new thread in the same process."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" (The tgkill syscall was designed to eliminate a similar race"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" condition in tkill, but it only succeeded in eliminating races"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" where the tid gets reused in a different process, and does not"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" help if the same tid gets assigned to a new thread in the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" same process.)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" The only solution I can see is to introduce a mutex that ensures"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" that a thread cannot exit while pthread_kill is being called on it."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" Note that in most real-world situations, like almost all race"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" conditions, this one will be extremely rare. To make it"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" measurable, one could exhaust all but 1-2 available pid values,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" possibly by lowering the max pid parameter in /proc, forcing"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" the same tid to be reused rapidly."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
